pageContext.claim: “How about the guy with the telephone? How about that one? I guarantee you that never took place. He said he's sitting there listening to me. I spoke so few times to him. But the guy yesterday on the telephone, David Holmes, 'Yes, I heard the conversation.' Well, I have really good hearing. And I've been watching guys for 40 years make phone calls. And I can't hear when -- you could be two feet away; I can't hear people making calls. I can't hear the other side, the phones up in the air. Unless you have it on the speaker phone, you can't do it. That was a total phony deal.
pageContext.analysis: Holmes testified that Sondland held the phone away from his ear because the president’s voice was so loud, which is how he was able to over hear the phone call.
